.TH DEMAKE\-INSPECT 1 "" "" "Analyze an image: is it compliant, for which consoles, and why not"
.SH NAME
demake-inspect \- Analyze an image: is it compliant, for which consoles, and why not
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdemake inspect\fR [\fIoptions\fR] [\fIinput\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Analyze an image: is it compliant, for which consoles, and why not.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-console\fR \fI<id>\fR
Check compliance for one console (default: all).
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-source\fR \fI<file>\fR
Also judge fidelity metrics vs this source image.
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit a single JSON object on stdout.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Increase diagnostic detail (repeatable).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
demake inspect out.png \-\-json
.PP
demake inspect out.png \-\-source photo.jpg \-\-json
.br
also score fidelity
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdemake\fR(1)
